  "riddle": "Here is the revised riddle:\n\n1. Seek the Wikipedia page about the footballer from Nepal who has played for the national team and is associated with clubs like the Army XI; which playing position does he occupy on the pitch?\n\n2. There exists a page that lays out Argentina's football pyramid; on that overview, how many cup competitions are recorded among its competitions?\n\n3. Before you move on, take the numeral you just uncovered from clue 2 and add its digits together — what total do those digits produce?\n\n4. If you consult a reputable world population source for Argentina, what population figure will it report for the nation as a whole?\n\n5. The article describing Argentina's second tier also names the regional divisions clubs drop into when relegated; identify one such division named there.\n\n6. In sun‑drenched Los Angeles the ground has an altitude — discover how many metres above sea level the city stands.\n\n7. The African club crown's 2015 edition kept a ledger of entrants; which number of teams is listed as having entered that continental competition?\n\n8. One map task (counting local lodgings): around latitude 49.284688 in Vancouver's historic waterfront neighbourhood, how many hotels can you find?\n\n9. As a mirror exercise, take the hotel count from clue 8 and reverse its digits — what new number do you obtain when those digits are read backwards?\n\n10. Finally, compute the digital root of (clue 4 + clue 7 + clue 8 + clue 9). Report that single digit (0–9) as your final answer.",
